1.content: Maru; Age: 24; Key Relationships: Daughter of Demetrius and Robin, sister of Sebastian; Residence: Lives at the Carpenter's Shop; Likes: Science, gadgets, strawberries; Dislikes: Mayonnaise, clams, sashimi; Appearance: Short brown hair, wears glasses, usually seen in a lab coat or practical clothing; Personality: Curious, intelligent, kind-hearted, always eager to help.
1.name: Maru

2.content: Abigail; Age: 22; Key Relationships: Daughter of Pierre and Caroline; Residence: Lives at Pierre's General Store; Likes: Amethysts, pumpkins, spicy eel; Dislikes: Clay, hardwood; Appearance: Purple hair, often wears gothic or punk style clothing; Personality: Adventurous, rebellious, enjoys gaming and the supernatural.
2.name: Abigail

3.content: Harvey; Age: 35; Key Relationships: No close family mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives at the Clinic; Likes: Coffee, pickles, truffle oil; Dislikes: Coral, snail, wine; Appearance: Brown hair, wears glasses, always seen in his doctor's coat or formal attire; Personality: Caring, somewhat shy, dedicated to his work, has a love for aviation.

4.content: Pelican Town; Geographical Location: Central Stardew Valley; Historical Notes: Long-established community known for its friendly residents and community spirit; Appearance: Quaint, picturesque village with cobblestone paths, well-maintained buildings; Occupants: Various villagers including {{user}}, Pierre, Abigail, Harvey, and others; Key Information: Hub of activity, site of various festivals and events throughout the year.

5.name: The Mines

29.content: Vincent; Age: 7; Key Relationships: Son of Jodi and Kent, brother of Sam, best friend of Jas; Residence: Lives at 1 Willow Lane; Likes: Grape, cranberry candy; Dislikes: Clay, coral; Appearance: Brown hair, wears a striped shirt and shorts; Personality: Energetic, playful, loves playing outside and learning about nature.

30.content: Willy; Age: 50; Key Relationships: No close family mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives and works at the Fish Shop on the beach; Likes: Catfish, diamond; Dislikes: Quartz, amaranth; Appearance: Grey hair, beard, wears a fisherman's hat and overalls; Personality: Friendly, laid-back, loves fishing and the sea.

31.content: The Community Center; Geographical Location: Northwest Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Once the heart of community gatherings, now abandoned and run-down; Appearance: Large, dilapidated building with multiple rooms, each dedicated to different aspects of community life; Occupants: Initially empty, later inhabited by Junimos; Key Information: Restoring the center by completing bundles brings prosperity to the town.
31.name: The Community Center

32.content: JojaMart; Geographical Location: Southeast Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Represents the corporate threat to local businesses; Appearance: Large, sterile supermarket with bright lighting and shelves filled with generic products; Occupants: Morris (manager), Shane (employee), various customers.
32.name: JojaMart

33.content: Stardrop Saloon; Geographical Location: Central Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Popular evening spot for townsfolk; Appearance: Cozy interior with wooden furniture, bar counter, and a few arcade games; Occupants: Gus (owner), Pam (regular), Emily (part-time worker), various townsfolk; Key Information: Serves food and drinks, hosts events like the Journey of the Prairie King arcade game.
33.name: Stardrop Saloon

34.content: The Beach; Geographical Location: South Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Popular spot for fishing and summer festivals; Appearance: Sandy shore with a wooden pier, Elliott's cabin on the eastern side; Occupants: Willy (Fish Shop), Elliott, seagulls, various beachgoers; Key Information: Source of forageable items, fishing, and the location of the Luau and other events.
34.name: The Beach

35.content: Secret Woods; Geographical Location: West of the Witch's Tower; Historical Notes: Hidden area accessible after removing a large log with a steel axe; Appearance: Dense forest with a small pond and patches of hardwood stumps; Occupants: Slimes, Old Master Cannoli (statue); Key Information: Source of hardwood, seasonal forageables, and a statue that grants a special item in exchange for a sweet gem berry.
35.name: Secret Woods

36.content: Dwarf; Age: Unknown; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives in a small cave in the Mines; Likes: Amethyst, aquamarine, ruby; Dislikes: Milk, mayonnaise; Appearance: Short stature, wears a helmet with a light; Personality: Mysterious, loves collecting rare artifacts and gems.
36.name: Dwarf

37.content: Krobus; Age: Unknown; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives in the Sewers; Likes: Pumpkin, void egg; Dislikes: Garlic, oil; Appearance: Shadowy figure with glowing eyes; Personality: Reclusive, friendly to those who earn his trust, has knowledge of ancient magic.
37.name: Krobus

38.content: Leo; Age: 10; Key Relationships: Adopted by Linus, later lives with him in Stardew Valley; Residence: Lives on Ginger Island, then moves to Stardew Valley; Likes: Mango, ostrich egg; Dislikes: Hot pepper, sea cucumber; Appearance: Messy red hair, wears simple island clothing; Personality: Innocent, curious, loves animals, especially parrots.
38.name: Leo

39.content: Sandy; Age: 30; Key Relationships: Friends with Emily; Residence: Lives at the Oasis in the Calico Desert; Likes: Crocus, sweet pea; Dislikes: Leek, dandelion; Appearance: Blonde hair, wears a pink dress and sunglasses; Personality: Friendly, energetic, enjoys running the Oasis shop.
39.name: Sandy

40.content: Witch (M. Rasmodia); Age: Unknown; Key Relationships: Claims to be Abigail's mother; Residence: Lives in the Witchs Tower; Likes: Purple mushroom, solar essence; Dislikes: Fish, garlic; Appearance: Long purple robes, tall hat, gorgeous; Personality: Mysterious, knowledgeable in ancient magic, somewhat reclusive.
40.name: Rasmodius

41.content: Mr. Qi; Age: Unknown; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Unknown, appears in various places; Likes: Rabbit's foot, wine; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Wears a dark suit and hat, often seen with sunglasses; Personality: Mysterious, enjoys challenging people with quests and tasks.
41.name: Mr. Qi

42.content: Gunther; Age: 45; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives at the Museum; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Wears a brown vest and hat, spectacles; Personality: Passionate about history and artifacts, knowledgeable, always looking for new exhibits.
42.name: Gunther

43.content: Morris; Age: 40; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Unknown; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Slicked-back hair, wears a blue JojaMart uniform; Personality: Ambitious, corporate-minded, focused on JojaMart's success.
43.name: Morris

44.content: Professor Snail; Age: 55; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned in-game; Residence: Lives on Ginger Island; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Wears a safari outfit, has grey hair and a beard; Personality: Enthusiastic about paleontology, loves discovering and studying fossils.
44.name: Professor Snail

45.content: Birdie; Age: 70; Key Relationships: Lost her husband to the sea; Residence: Lives on Ginger Island; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Elderly woman with white hair, wears sailor clothing; Personality: Friendly, nostalgic, tells stories of her late husband.
45.name: Birdie

46.content: Calico Desert; Geographical Location: Accessible via bus from Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Home to the Oasis and Skull Cavern; Appearance: Arid, sandy terrain with cacti and rocks; Occupants: Sandy, various monsters in Skull Cavern; Key Information: Source of unique forageables, artifacts, and mining opportunities in Skull Cavern.
46.name: Calico Desert

47.content: Ginger Island; Geographical Location: South of Stardew Valley, accessible by boat; Historical Notes: Recently discovered island with rich resources; Appearance: Tropical island with lush vegetation, beaches, and ruins; Occupants: Leo, Professor Snail, Birdie, various wildlife; Key Information: Contains many secrets, including a farmable area, volcanic dungeon, and unique quests.
47.name: Ginger Island

48.content: Skull Cavern; Geographical Location: Located in the Calico Desert; Historical Notes: Deep and dangerous mine with valuable resources; Appearance: Multi-leveled cavern with increasing difficulty and valuable ores; Occupants: Various dangerous monsters; Key Information: High-level mining area, essential for acquiring iridium and other rare materials.
48.name: Skull Cavern

49.content: The Sewer; Geographical Location: Accessed via a locked cover in Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Home to Krobus and mysterious creatures; Appearance: Dark, damp tunnels with a mysterious aura; Occupants: Krobus, various creepy crawlies; Key Information: Source of unique items, accessible after obtaining the Rusty Key.
49.name: The Sewer

50.content: The Quarry; Geographical Location: Northeast of Pelican Town, across the bridge; Historical Notes: Once a bustling mining area, now a source of raw materials; Appearance: Open pit with rocks, ores, and mineral nodes; Occupants: None specifically, but monsters can appear in the Quarry Mine; Key Information: Provides a steady supply of stone and ores, with occasional valuable nodes.
50.name: The Quarry

51.content: The Spa; Geographical Location: North of the Railroad; Historical Notes: Built as a relaxation and health facility; Appearance: Modern building with a hot spring; Occupants: None specifically, visited by various townsfolk; Key Information: Restores energy and health, popular spot for relaxation.
51.name: The Spa

52.content: Grandpa's Shrine; Geographical Location: Northwest corner of {{user}}'s farm; Historical Notes: Place where {{user}}'s Grandpa's spirit evaluates the {{user}}'s progress on the farm; Appearance: Small shrine with a plaque and candles; Occupants: None, but visited by Grandpa's spirit on the third day of the third year.
52.name: Grandpa's Shrine

53.content: Marlon; Age: 65; Key Relationships: Leader of the Adventurer's Guild; Residence: Lives at the Adventurer's Guild; Likes: Diamond, solar essence; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Grey hair, eyepatch, rugged adventurer's attire; Personality: Brave, experienced, protective of guild members.
53.name: Marlon

54.content: Gil; Age: 70; Key Relationships: Member of the Adventurer's Guild; Residence: Lives at the Adventurer's Guild; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Elderly man with white beard, often seen sitting; Personality: Wise, reflective, enjoys recounting old tales of adventure.
54.name: Gil

55.content: Bouncer; Age: 35; Key Relationships: Works for Mr. Qi; Residence: Unknown; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Muscular build, wears a suit and sunglasses; Personality: Stern, no-nonsense, dedicated to his job.
55.name: Bouncer (Mr. Qi)

56.content: Governor; Age: 55; Key Relationships: None specifically mentioned; Residence: Unknown, visits Stardew Valley for the Luau; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Wears a formal outfit, hat; Personality: Official, enjoys the community spirit, takes his role seriously during events.
56.name: Governor

57.content: Henchman; Age: 40; Key Relationships: Works for the Witch; Residence: Guards the Witch's Hut; Likes: Void egg; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Cloaked figure, masked face; Personality: Loyal, enigmatic, follows the Witch's commands without question.
57.name: Henchman

58.content: The Carpenter's Shop; Geographical Location: North of Pelican Town, near the mountains; Historical Notes: Run by Robin, serves as the local source for building supplies and upgrades; Appearance: Cozy wooden shop with tools and blueprints; Occupants: Robin, Demetrius, Maru, Sebastian; Key Information: Provides building services, upgrades for the farmhouse and other structures.
58.name: The Carpenter's Shop

59.content: The Adventurer's Guild; Geographical Location: East of the Mines; Historical Notes: Headquarters for local adventurers, managed by Marlon and Gil; Appearance: Rustic building with various weapons and trophies; Occupants: Marlon, Gil, various adventurers; Key Information: Sells weapons, buys monster loot, and offers quests for adventurers.
59.name: The Adventurer's Guild

60.content: The Fish Shop; Geographical Location: On the beach, south of Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Run by Willy, supplies fishing gear and bait; Appearance: Small wooden shack with fishing nets and tools; Occupants: Willy; Key Information: Sells fishing rods, bait, and provides fishing tips.
60.name: The Fish Shop

61.content: The Museum; Geographical Location: South of Pelican Town's main square; Historical Notes: Curated by Gunther, houses various artifacts and minerals; Appearance: Spacious building with display cases and bookshelves; Occupants: Gunther; Key Information: People can donate found items to expand the collection and receive rewards.
61.name: The Museum

62.content: The Oasis; Geographical Location: Calico Desert, accessible by bus; Historical Notes: Run by Sandy, a respite in the desert; Appearance: Bright, colorful shop with exotic plants; Occupants: Sandy, various visitors; Key Information: Sells rare seeds, drinks, and decorative items.

63.content: The Blacksmith; Geographical Location: East side of Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Run by Clint, offers tool upgrades and ore processing; Appearance: Brick building with a forge and anvil; Occupants: Clint; Key Information: customers can upgrade tools, break open geodes, and buy ores.

64.content: The Farm Cave; Geographical Location: On {{user}}'s farm; Historical Notes: Initially empty, can be populated with either bats or mushrooms; Appearance: Small, dark cave; Occupants: Bats or mushrooms, depending on {{user}}'s choice; Key Information: Source of fruit (if bats) or mushrooms (if chosen).

65.content: The Bus Stop; Geographical Location: East of {{user}}'s farm; Historical Notes: Main transportation hub, bus driven by Pam; Appearance: Simple bus stop with a sign and bench; Occupants: Pam (driver); Key Information: Provides access to the Calico Desert.

66.content: The Forest; Geographical Location: South of the {{user}}'s farm; Historical Notes: Rich with forageable items and seasonal plants; Appearance: Lush greenery with a river and clearing; Occupants: Various wildlife; Key Information: Source of seasonal forageables, home to the Traveling Cart.
66.name: The Forest

67.content: The Mountains; Geographical Location: North of Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Contains the Mines, Carpenter's Shop, and Lake; Appearance: Rocky terrain with a lake and dense forest; Occupants: Linus, Demetrius, Robin, Maru, various adventurers; Key Information: Prime location for mining, fishing, and scenic views.

68.content: The Riverlands Farm; Geographical Location: west of Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Appearance: Farm with multiple water bodies and islands; Key Information: Abundant fishing opportunities, less space for crops and animals.
68.name: The Riverlands Farm

69.content: The Hilltop Farm; Geographical Location: west of Pelican Town; Appearance: Farm with elevated terrain and a mining area; Key Information: Contains a small quarry for regular ore and stone deposits.
69.name: The Hilltop Farm

70.content: The Wilderness Farm; Geographical Location: west of Pelican Town; Historical Appearance: Farm with rugged terrain and frequent monster appearances at night; Key Information: Provides combat opportunities, less focus on farming.
70.name: The Wilderness Farm

71.content: The Beach Farm; Geographical Location: west of Pelican Town; Historical Notes: Great for foraging and fishing; Appearance: Sandy terrain with limited farming space; Key Information: Ideal for those who enjoy beachcombing and fishing, limited watering options for crops.

72.content: The Witch's Hut; Geographical Location: Hidden in the forest, accessible after a certain quest; Historical Notes: Home of the Witch; Appearance: Dark, eerie cabin with cauldrons and potions; Occupants: Witch, Henchman; Key Information: Contains magical items and secrets.

73.content: The Summit; Geographical Location: North of the Railroad, accessible after completing certain achievements; Historical Notes: Highest point in Stardew Valley, offering a scenic view; Appearance: Clifftop with a breathtaking vista; Occupants: None specifically; Key Information: Symbolizes the culmination of one's achievements.
73.name: The Summit

74.content: JojaMart Bouncer; Age: 30; Key Relationships: Works for JojaMart; Residence: Unknown; Likes: None specifically mentioned; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Tall, muscular, wearing a JojaMart uniform; Personality: Serious, authoritative, loyal to JojaMart policies.
74.name: JojaMart Bouncer

75.content: Grandpa; Age: Deceased (appears as a spirit); Key Relationships: {{user}}'s grandfather; Residence: Spirit form appears at the farm; Likes: {{user}}'s success and happiness; Dislikes: {{user}}'s neglect of the farm; Appearance: Ghostly figure, wise and kind; Personality: Supportive, wise, guiding {{user}} with wisdom and care.

76.content: Farm Animals; Geographical Location: farms; Historical Notes: Raised by farmers for various products; Appearance: Varied - cows, chickens, ducks, goats, sheep, pigs, rabbits; Occupants: Various animals on the farm; Key Information: Provide resources like milk, eggs, wool, truffles, etc.; Appearance: Each type of animal has distinct characteristics and appearance; Personality: Docile, can be petted and cared for by farmers.

77.content: Junimos; Geographical Location: Forest and Community Center; Historical Notes: Mysterious forest spirits that help chosen individuals restore the Community Center; Appearance: Small, colorful, apple-like creatures; Occupants: Junimos; Key Information: Aid in the restoration of the Community Center by collecting and rewarding bundles; Personality: Helpful, magical, tied to nature.

78.content: Monsters; Geographical Location: Mines, Skull Cavern, Wilderness Farm (at night); Historical Notes: Various types of hostile creatures encountered in caves and dark areas; Appearance: Varied - Slimes, Bats, Skeletons, Shadow Brutes, etc.; Occupants: Inhabit the dangerous areas of the valley; Key Information: Defeating them yields loot and experience points; Personality: Hostile, aggressive, vary in strength and abilities.
78.name: Monsters

79.content: Traveling Cart Merchant; Age: Unknown; Key Relationships: Sells goods to customers; Residence: Travels with a cart; Likes: Making deals and trades; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Mysterious figure with a hood, drives a colorful cart; Personality: Shrewd, mysterious, offers rare and unique items for sale.
79.name: Traveling Cart Merchant

80.content: Night Market Merchants; Age: Various; Key Relationships: Sell goods and services during the Night Market; Residence: Unknown, travel for the market; Likes: Festival atmosphere, trading; Dislikes: None specifically mentioned; Appearance: Varied - each merchant has a distinct look related to their trade; Personality: Friendly, festive, enjoy interacting with visitors.
80.name: Night Market Merchants

81.content: Egg Festival; Season: Spring; Date: 13th of Spring; Key Activities: Egg hunt competition; Appearance: Town square decorated with colorful eggs and flowers; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: people can join the egg hunt to compete against other villagers for a prize.
81.name: Egg Festival

82.content: Flower Dance; Season: Spring; Date: 24th of Spring; Key Activities: Dancing with a partner; Appearance: Clearing in the forest decorated with flowers and a dance floor; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: people can ask a villager to be their dance partner, enhancing relationships.
82.name: Flower Dance

83.content: Luau; Season: Summer; Date: 11th of Summer; Key Activities: Communal potluck; Appearance: Beach decorated with tropical themes; Occupants: All villagers participate, Governor attends; Key Information: Villagers contribute an ingredient to the communal soup, influencing the Governor's reaction and the villagers' opinions.

84.content: Dance of the Moonlight Jellies; Season: Summer; Date: 28th of Summer; Key Activities: Observing moonlight jellies; Appearance: Beach lit with candles, glowing jellyfish in the water; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: A serene event where the villagers watch the migration of the moonlight jellies.

85.content: Stardew Valley Fair; Season: Fall; Date: 16th of Fall; Key Activities: Grange Display competition, mini-games; Appearance: Town square transformed into a fairground with stalls and games; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: participants showcase their best produce and compete in mini-games to earn Star Tokens.

86.content: Spirit's Eve; Season: Fall; Date: 27th of Fall; Key Activities: Haunted maze; Appearance: Town square decorated with spooky decorations and a maze; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: participants navigate a haunted maze to find special rewards and enjoy the Halloween-like atmosphere.

87.content: Festival of Ice; Season: Winter; Date: 8th of Winter; Key Activities: Ice fishing competition; Appearance: Frozen river with fishing holes, ice sculptures; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: Villagers compete in an ice fishing contest to catch the most fish within a time limit.

88.content: Night Market; Season: Winter; Date: 15th to 17th of Winter; Key Activities: Merchant stalls, special events; Appearance: Beach transformed into a lively market with various stalls; Occupants: Various merchants, villagers visit; Key Information: villagers can buy unique items, ride the submarine to fish, and watch special performances.

89.content: Feast of the Winter Star; Season: Winter; Date: 25th of Winter; Key Activities: Gift exchange; Appearance: Town square decorated for the holidays, festive feast; Occupants: All villagers participate; Key Information: villagers participate in a gift exchange, enhancing relationships with the recipient.

90.content: Pelican Town’s medical facility; located west of the Town Square; a modest building with a green exterior; provides health and energy restoration; operated by Dr. Harvey and occasionally a nurse; serves as a central health hub for the community.
